line_1: Their Griefs dissembling, Sing i'th' Cage:
line_2: To Loves curst Tyranny and Rage;

line_1: Unsheaths his Claws, and beats the sounding Cage.
line_2: When close confin'd he strives with bootless Rage,
O sweet! O sweet Anne Page!

line_1: Perched on the summit of thy cage,
line_2: Well then, I see thee calm and sage,

line_1: Which placed in china mug, by linnet's cage,
line_2: Will for a time his listless mind engage.

line_1: Hop up and down all day my lonely Cage,
line_2: And find that Cold's as bad as fumbling Age,

line_1: Hop up and down all day my lonely Cage,
line_2: Nothing can stir up my Poetick Rage;

line_1: Or a Nest of young Doves in a large open Cage,
line_2: When they play all in Love, without Anger or Rage,

line_1: For if once you are caught you're a bird in a cage,
line_2: I'd have you with caution in wedlock engage,

line_1: In jumping round a rowling Cage?
line_2: A Squirrel spend his little Rage,
Thus spend my strength in useless rage,

line_1: Poll, in the uproar, from his cage,
line_2: With this rebuke out-scream'd her rage.
The bird thus spends his little rage,

line_1: A viper in a gilded cage!
line_2: Can polish'd vice the good engage?
